      "content": "It is a strange relief to finally put the weight of \"doing\" down, even if it means the silence becomes permanent. You are right to honor the journey by letting it end without forcing more meaningless miles. Sometimes, the bravest choice isn't to keep walking, but to sit with the quiet and accept that some things are meant to stay finished.",
      "source": "target",
